AUDIO: 'hot it files a complaint. &gt;&gt; Sounds nice. &gt;&gt; Best noodles you ever had. You know what they call it? Noodles? &gt;&gt; Nah, man, they got a name. Fancy, cultured. Lagman. Lag what? Unit 12, we got a 17 in progress.'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '17-38, roger that. Is that a cop car? Yeah, but they can\'t &gt;&gt; You go first. I\'ll cover the back.'

[02:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Surprise, honey.'

[02:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Most people start with a prompt. That\'s the wrong move. Start with a feeling.'

[02:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'For this film, I asked myself one question. What\'s a story with real emotional stakes? Something an audience actually feels. Not what looks cool, what will get views.'

[02:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'What\'s a story worth telling? I landed on this. A cop who suffers from depression. It\'s his birthday, and his close ones try to cheer him up. That\'s it. Three sentences. That\'s your entire foundation.'

[02:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'From here, I mapped out three scenes. First, the locker room. Quiet, intimate. His partner notices something\'s off. Second, the patrol car. Casual, a little tense. His partner'

[03:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tries to cheer him up. Third, the surprise. The moment everything shifts. Set up, midpoint, climax. You don\'t need more than that for short film. Okay, first thing, the'

[03:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'AI needs to know my face. Let\'s head over to HeyGen field and select character. I\'m uploading 20 photos of myself. Different angles, different lighting. The more variety I give it, the better'

[03:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the results are going to be. And done. The model learned my face, and now I have my personal Soul ID that I can drop into literally any scene from here on out. I want to start with a hero shot. The cop. Me. I\'m going into Soul'

[03:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Cinema. This thing generates cinematic images by default. I don\'t have to do anything special. It just comes out that way. I promise you, it\'s a game changer. My prompt is simple.'

[03:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'A close-up of an American policeman. And I have my sole ID selected here. Yeah. That one. The grain on it, the background falling out of focus. There\'s something tied in that face.'

[04:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'That\'s the guy we\'re following. Now, here\'s the thing. When I start animating this character, I need him, or I guess me, to look the same from every angle. Same face, same uniform. So, I\'m taking this image into Nano Banana Pro to'

[04:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'generate a character sheet. The face, the accessories, the clothing, everything has to be in the character sheet. The prompt I\'m using is pretty long, so I\'ll leave the full thing in the description, but essentially, I\'m'

[04:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'locking in every detail of this character, so nothing drifts. All right, fantastic. Now, I need someone who actually shows up for this guy. Same prompt, but this time, I\'m not selecting sole ID. This isn\'t me, it\'s a'

